What I changed\
\
schema_v4.py: Added VoiceConfigV4 and a voice field on BookPlanV4 (optional, default disabled).\
section_assembler.py:\
Added _insert_voice_bridges hook after story/exercise injection and before character substitution.\
Bridges are loaded via cluster_therapy_tok.runtime.voice_pack_loader and selected deterministically (seeded by book/chapter/section).\
Validation: max 2 sentences; skips if forbidden lexicon is hit; fails open (voice never blocks a book).\
Hook is no-op unless book_plan.voice.enabled is true.\
Assembly succeeds with existing plans (voice omitted 
\f17 \'81\'cb
\f0  disabled).\
How to use (optional)\
\
Add to your plan YAML (top-level):\
voice:\
  enabled: true\
  locale: en_US          # or your pack id\
  voice_pack_id: en_US   # optional explicit pack\
  persona: gen_z         # optional\
  dialect_config:\
    generation: gen_z    # passed through; not applied in text\
Re-assemble. If the voice pack exists (e.g., en_US_voice_pack_v1.yaml), short hook/close bridges will appear; otherwise voice is skipped silently.\
