---\
\
## Short answer\
\

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  **Yes, formats are compatible**\

\f2 \uc0\u9888 \u65039 
\f0  **Not by copying the Raising assembler**\

\f2 \uc0\u9989 
\f0  **By treating formats as plan-level structural schemas**\
\
Omega V4 already has **90% of what formats need**. What\'92s missing is a **format abstraction layer that compiles into a normal V4 plan**.\
\
---\
\
## Key principle (non-negotiable)\
\
> **Formats must resolve into a standard 
\f3\fs28 \cb8 BookPlanV4
\f0\fs32 \cb7  before assembly.**\
\
Omega V4 does **not**:\
\
* assemble at runtime\
* mutate content during render\
* allow format logic to bypass validation\
\
So formats must exist **upstream**, at **plan-generation time**, not assembly time.\
\
This is good news \'97 it keeps V4 clean.\
\
---\
\
## How Raising formats map cleanly to V4\
\
Let\'92s translate concepts:\
\
| Phoenix Raising     | Omega V4 equivalent             |\
| ------------------- | ------------------------------- |\
| Format wrapper      | **Plan schema template**        |\
| Format assembler    | **Plan compiler**               |\
| Day / ritual step   | **ChapterPlanV4**               |\
| Wrapper sections    | **SectionPlanV4 (role-tagged)** |\
| Platform adaptation | **Post-assembly export step**   |\
| Modules             | **Optional appended chapters**  |\
\
Nothing here conflicts with V4.\
\
